reviews.text:
No idea what the goal is, outside the obvious goal of doing less work;
I called looking for an atty for a pretty open/shut police misconduct case and was immediately directed to fill out an endless form detailing entire life history (Education, spouse info, marriages, kids info, employment history, etc, etc, etc) and asks you to indicate what the basis of your claim is...like no one needs an attorney to determine that. I've been looking for representation for 2 years. I'm not spending 2 hours filling out a form to be told they don't practice that kind of law/need to refer/wrong part of the state.
If anyone knows an actual, tangible attorney that wants a fairly easy case for good money, PLEASE have them find me on Facebook and reach out
